 @{bg shine}:.I.:@{bg back}

 @{b}@{u}Game Over für Phase 5:@{ub}@{uu}

 Eine bittere Pille,die wir diesen Monat schlucken müssen...

--@{i}Oberursel, 09.02.2000:
 Über das Vermögen der phase 5 digital production
 ist am 26.01.2000 Insolvenzantrag gestellt worden, und per Beschluß des
 zuständigen Amtsgerichts vom gleichen Tag das Insolvenzantragsverfahren
 eröffnet worden. Im Zuge des laufenden Verfahrens wird derzeit u.a. mit
 Interessenten über eine Übernahme und Weiterführung der
 AMIGA-Technologiesparte verhandelt. Damit soll eine Weiterführung der
 laufenden Entwicklungen und Produkte, speziell der neuen
 G4-Prozessorkarten, erreicht werden.
 Alle Kunden, die Bestellungen und Anzahlungen an die phase 5 digital
 products geleistet haben, werden im Falle der Eröffnung des
 Insolvenzverfahrens über ihre Rechte informiert und angeschrieben.@{ui}--

 @{u}- Quelle: www.amiga-news.de -@{uu}


 @{bg shine}:.II.:@{bg back}

 @{b}@{u}Bill McEwen informiert:@{ub}@{uu}

--@{i}February 3, 2000

 A great deal has occurred over the last couple of weeks, and it is
 only going to get hotter as we move forward. In the last two weeks
 we have announced our new OS partner, began technical
 training and began meetings with future technology partners.
 The response has been overwhelming, and we are but keeping our heads
 above water.
 On January 8, 2000 at CES in Las Vegas we announced our partnership
 with Tao-Group as our foundation OS partner. This is a strategic
 relationship and brings us great rewards. I have asked Fleecy to write
 a short document highlighting the Amiga/Tao relationship from a more
 technical perspective, other than my telling everyone how incredible
 great and fantastic it is. In the next two weeks we will make another
 strategic partnership announcement with regards to the new Amiga and
 the operating system.
 After a week long trip to Germany and England I have come back with a
 much better understanding of what we can not do. As mentioned before
 we are not going to make promises or product announcements. We will
 announce to you, the community, only after the deal is signed. This@{ui}
 @{i}will help preclude from the continuance of rumors, and the continued
 deterioration of the Amiga.
 Our job as a company is to create exciting market opportunities for
 Amiga developers to take advantage of, and Amiga users to enjoy. This
 is more than just an upgrade to the OS. This is a complete strategy
 involving all aspects of the business.
 Many of you have sent us business proposals, and product marketing
 ideas, for this we thank you, and ask your patience as we look over
 these plans. Some of them offer us some good ideas and perspective
 into areas and desires of the Amiga community as a whole that we may
 not have considered.
 Over the next several weeks there will be some companies that come
 out with their own plans, or state that we do not have the community
 at heart as we move on. The reality is, they do not know what we
 have planned. In order to keep focused and to keep the incredible
 pace up and moving we are not sharing our plans outside of our signed
 partnerships. This means that if you hear something that you have not
 read on our site, or from a member of our team directly, it is not
 true.
 Plain and simple. If you did not hear it from us, or read it here on@{ui}
 @{i}this web site it is not true. We are not asking for your trust or your
 undying belief. We only ask that you take us on our words and deeds.
 We will begin official meetings in Germany, England and the US for
 developers and dealers. This will include introductory training
 seminars for the new OS, and introductions to the retail pricing
 and schedules. We will also begin the process of bringing out the new
 web site, and more details will emerge as this happens.
 I want to thank each and everyone of you for your hospitality during
 our meetings and your continued opportunities for us to move forward.
 We have had the chance to meet with end users, developers, dealers,
 and new partners.
 There is a great deal of activity, and some great things happening.
 New partners, old faces joining the team, and we are already in the
 process of moving into bigger facilities.

 Keeping the faith,

 Bill McEwen and the rest of the Amiga Team@{ui}--



